      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Norway's 2 petabytes of Huawei flash storage and LLM training",
      "url": "https://www.blocksandfiles.com/flash/2026/05/22/norways-2-petabytes-of-huawei-flash-storage-and-llm-training/5244910",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48270770",
      "score": 184,
      "comments": 89,
      "author": "rbanffy",
      "published": "2026-05-25T19:37:57Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Norway’s National Library acquired 2 petabytes of Huawei OceanStor flash storage to power sovereign Norwegian language model (LLM) training.",
        "High-throughput NVMe storage is critical for feeding large datasets to GPUs during the pre-training phases of models like NorBERT.",
        "The deal underscores European AI infrastructure dependencies and security debates over deploying Huawei hardware in national public sector projects."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "A Simple Makefile Tutorial (2008)",
      "url": "https://cs.colby.edu/maxwell/courses/tutorials/maketutor/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/owa9kn",
      "score": 13,
      "comments": 11,
      "author": "kenballus",
      "published": "2026-05-25T14:44:03Z",
      "bullets": [
        "GNU Make automates compilation by tracking file modification times to rebuild only modified dependencies and targets.",
        "Using variables like `CC` and `CFLAGS` centralizes compiler selection and build flags for consistent, portable compilation.",
        "Pattern rules like `%.o: %.c` reduce redundancy, while `.PHONY` prevents conflicts with actual files for commands like `clean`."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "How my minimal, memory-safe Go rsync steers clear of vulnerabilities",
      "url": "https://michael.stapelberg.ch/posts/2026-05-24-minimal-memory-safe-go-rsync-vulns/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/5y9u93",
      "score": 93,
      "comments": 17,
      "author": "stapelberg",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:38:34Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Rewriting rsync in Go eliminates memory corruption vulnerabilities like buffer overflows and use-after-free errors common in legacy C implementations.",
        "A minimal implementation reduces attack surface by excluding complex legacy protocol features that frequently lead to remote code execution.",
        "Leveraging Go's strict native path handling mitigates directory traversal risks, a historical vulnerability vector in traditional file transfer tools."
      ]
    },
    {
